<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-08-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="45" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d45">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mizner</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-04"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 4,
                            1890</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Wharton informs Mr. Ryan of the receipt of Mr. Mizner’s telegram of the
                        1st instant, through the legation in Mexico, and instructs him to telegraph
                        Mr. Mizner that the Department considers it necessary for him to go to San
                        José and place himself in communication with the Government of Salvador
                        through the United States naval vessels at that port, as well as with the
                        Guatemalan Government, in order that he may offer his good offices to both
                        countries.</p>
